HEADWORD: Sweepstake
<hw>Sweep"stake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
winning of all the stakes or prizes.</def> <rj><au>Heylin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A complete removal or carrying away; a clean
sweep.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hacket.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweepstakes</ent>⟦br⟧
